Bowling Alley LLD - Clear Flow


1) Core Entities
- Roll
  - Stores one roll value: `pins_knocked` (0 to 10).
  - Only roll-level validation.

- Frame (abstract)
  - Common behavior for all frame types.
  - Holds rolls and helpers: `is_strike`, `is_spare`, `pins_knocked`.

- NormalFrame (frames 1 to 9)
  - Max 2 rolls.
  - Strike ends frame immediately.
  - Two-roll sum cannot exceed 10.

- FinalFrame (frame 10)
  - Normally 2 rolls.
  - Third roll allowed only if spare/strike in first two rolls.
  - Max 3 rolls with final-frame constraints.

2) Player
- Owns exactly 10 frames: 9 NormalFrame + 1 FinalFrame.
- `roll(pins)`: sends roll to current incomplete frame.
- Scoring rules (standard bowling):
  - Open frame: frame pins only.
  - Spare: 10 + next 1 roll.
  - Strike: 10 + next 2 rolls.
  - Final frame: sum of its own rolls only.
- Exposes:
  - `total_score()`
  - `frame_scores()` (running totals)
  - `is_game_complete()`

3) Game (Single Lane Game)
- Owns multiple players.
- Tracks current player turn.
- On each roll:
  - apply roll to current player
  - if current frame is now complete, move to next player
  - else same player rolls again
- Exposes:
  - `scores()`
  - `running_scores()`
  - `winner()` (after game complete)

  //Out of scope or include if interviewer ask for extensability of this game

4) Lane
- One lane can have at most one active game.
- Can start a new game only when lane is free.
- Routes rolls to its active game.

5) BowlingAlleySystem
- Manages multiple lanes in parallel.
- Start game on specific lane or any free lane.
- Route roll by lane id.
- Check free lane ids.

6) Runtime Flow
- Create `BowlingAlleySystem(lane_count)`.
- Start game(s) with players on lane(s).
- For each turn, call `system.roll(lane_id, pins)`.
- Game handles player turn switching automatically.
- During game, read running scores from `game.running_scores()`.
- At end, call `game.winner()`.

7) Design Principles Used
- SRP:
  - Roll validates roll
  - Frame validates frame constraints
  - Player calculates score
  - Game handles turn order
  - Lane/System handle orchestration
- KISS:
  - Straightforward classes and methods.
- YAGNI:
  - No extra layers (DB/UI/events) added now.
- Extensibility:
  - Can add different scoring strategy or UI layer later without changing core flow.
